@nickpan47 Thanks much for the timely review! I have updated the patch to address all comments.

On the Kafka side, https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4462 is the umbrella patch that makes sure the 0.11 client can talk to broker with version 0.10.2 or later. https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-4548 added integration tests (executed with Vagrant and Docker) which verified that new client can talk to old broker.

I think we can manually test that Samza compiled with Kafka 0.11 can work with Kafka 0.10.2 or later. But it may take a lot of work to add integration test for this in Samza. Currently Samza's integration test will always use the same version of Kafka client library as the version of the Kafka cluster it starts. We will probably need similar integration test framework as Kafka (with Vagrant and Docker) to do this compatibility test.
